f=Executive Office/marcus/operational/agent/marcus-config.md · p=Machine-readable configuration marcus skill files reference deliberately don't hardcode escalation thresholds, escalation routing, any model/tool preferences. stripped VYON-specific values during genericization (per portability goal) need real values filled deployment rather invented here. · h2:Config Template=`# --- Escalation --- \· escalation_threshold: \· spend_usd: <FILL_IN>              # e.g. 5000 — dollar amount above which decision-critic/ \· # venture-priority-matrix must escalate rather than recommend directly \· irreversibility_rule: <FILL_IN>   # e.g. "any decision that can't be unwound within 30 days"` · in=`<FILL_IN>` replaced real value, explicitly marked `n/a` one-line reason, before marcus's escalation behavior trusted production until then, treat skill's "escalate board" instruction "escalate operator directly" safe default. Values stay generic enough reusable across different deployments agent system (per portability goal) file one place venture/company-specific numbers belong, skill files themselves. values change (e.g. escalation threshold revised), update file skill files reference "the agreed threshold" rather restating number, they don't need touched. · f=Until file filled in, marcus state explicitly decision normally trigger escalation, rather silently defaulting either "always escalate" "never escalate."